com.vmware.vcenter

Interface ResourcePool

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ResourcePoolTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourcePoolStub

    public interface ResourcePool
extends Service, ResourcePoolTypes
    The ResourcePool interface provides methods for manipulating a vCenter Server resource pool.

    This interface does not include virtual appliances in the inventory of resource pools even though part of the behavior of a virtual appliance is to act like a resource pool.

        Retrieves information about the resource pool indicated by resourcePool.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

      • list

        java.util.List<ResourcePoolTypes.Summary> list(ResourcePoolTypes.FilterSpec filter)
        Returns information about at most 1000 visible (subject to permission checks) resource pools in vCenter matching the ResourcePoolTypes.FilterSpec.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        filter - Specification of matching resource pools for which information should be returned. If null, the behavior is equivalent to a ResourcePoolTypes.FilterSpec with all properties null which means all resource pools match the filter.
        Returns:
        Commonly used information about the resource pools matching the ResourcePoolTypes.FilterSpec.
        Throws:
        UnableToAllocateResource - if more than 1000 resource pools match the ResourcePoolTypes.FilterSpec.
        ServiceUnavailable - if the system is unable to communicate with a service to complete the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have the required privileges.
